Package com.irurueta.navigation.frames

Class CoordinateTransformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.navigation.frames.CoordinateTransformation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class CoordinateTransformation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Contains a coordinate transformation matrix, or rotation matrix. The coordinate transformation matrix is a 3x3 matrix where a vector may be transformed in one step from one set of resolving axes to another by pre-multiplying it by the appropriate coordinate transformation matrix. The coordinate transformation matrix is associated to a source and destination frame. This implementation is based on the equations defined in "Principles of GNSS, Inertial, and Multisensor Integrated Navigation Systems, Second Edition" and on the companion software available at: https://github.com/ymjdz/MATLAB-Codes/blob/master/Euler_to_CTM.m https://github.com/ymjdz/MATLAB-Codes/blob/master/CTM_to_Euler.m
    See Also:
